<div class = "container">
	<h1>About Beehive</h1>

  <div class = "card">
    <p>
      <b>Story</b>: Beehive is an open-source project originally sponsored by the College of Engineering. It was started as a CS 169 (then CS 194-4) project in Fall 2009 under Prof. Armando Fox. Currently, Beehive's development is under the management of the <a href="http://asucocto.org" target="_blank">ASUC Office of the CTO</a>, and its <a href="https://github.com/asuc-octo/Beehive" target="_blank">source code</a> and full <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1LN0ILxUudn9Q7nUrPh5X6h8teRxeGMdbP9eQGIFN7FM/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">product specs</a> are available for public perusal.
    </p>

    <p>
  		<b>Vision</b>: Open access to research, for everyone. As a year-round, student-run platform for undergraduate research at Berkeley, we aim to fill the gaps left behind existing programs like URAP, SURF, and SPUR, which typically provide opportunities on a cyclical basis and have dedicated administrative staff. In addition, we also reach out to students and faculty to encourage higher participation in research.
  	</p>

